The earliest evidence of eukaryotic life dates back approximately 1.85 billion years. While it is possible that eukaryotes existed prior to this, their diversification is believed to have accelerated with the advent of oxygen-utilizing metabolic processes. Around 1.7 billion years ago, multicellular organisms began to emerge, featuring differentiated cells that performed specialized functions.
